#### IMPORTTANT #### 
Your classes must respect the **Coplien form**.
####

[X] • The executable will be named MattDaemon.
[X] • The program will have to run only with the root rights.
[X] • Your program will have to run in the background, just like a real daemon.
[X] • The daemon will have to listen to the port 4242.
[X] • For your daemon’s log, you will have to create a class called Tintin_reporter (you
will be able to re-use it in future projects).
[X] • Every daemon action should show in a log file matt_daemon.log with timestamp
(in this form [ DD / MM / YYYY - HH : MM : SS]) located in the folder /var/log/-
matt_daemon/.
[X] • Only one daemon instance should be able to run at once.
[X] • When attempting to run a second daemon whereas one instance is already running,
an error message indicating a creation/file opening on matt_daemon.lock attempt
must pop.
[X] • A matt_daemon.lock file must be created in /var/lock/ when the daemon starts.
[X] • When the daemon shuts down, the matt_daemon.lock file must be deleted. `
[X] • The program must quit with the sending of a simple "quit" character chain on the
opened socket.
[X] • Any other character chain must be registered in the log file.
[] • Only 3 clients can connect simultaneously to the daemon.
[] • When the daemon receives a signal, it must intercept it and register it in the
matt_daemon.log file with an explicit message and quit properly.
